<dl id="un1013l"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="un1" href="#un1013">UN1: </a>  <a href="../../FF/unbs/un1all.htm#un1013l"> (NLI.3) 13(l)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> pralaya (path of return): <small>Red</small></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <ul class="list-inline" id="un1013l"><li>Ulysses </li><li><a href="../../ulex/n/lexn.htm#un1013l">2021</a> </li><li><a href="../../ulex/n/n86.htm#un1013l">2017</a> </li><li><a href="../../ulex/n/n86.htm#un1013l">1986 (12.346)</a> </li><li><a href="../../ulex/n/l22n.htm#un1013l">1922</a> </li><li><ms href="#un1013l">MS V.A.8-5v</ms> </li><li>JJA 13:094 </li><li><a name="n1B1d" href="../udra/u12da.htm#n1B1d">Usage</a> </li><li><a href="../../ulex/n/n1B1d.htm#un1013l">Draft: 12B.1</a></li> </ul> <blockquote class="sources">True Will-power is surely the power and energy of the whole, as much on the physical plane and on the &ldquo;path of outgoing,&rdquo; as on the Buddhic plane and the <mark>&ldquo;path of return&rdquo;</mark>; it actually is that very rhythmical swing which makes those outward and returning paths&mdash;those sargas and <mark>pralayas</mark>&mdash;and that which is gained by the limited J&iuml;va by cultivation of Truth and Poise is surely a wider consciousness, a consciousness in which he has a sense of oneness with the organic whole, whose consciousness is this Will-power, accompanied by the knowledge that much that appears to his still limited consciousness has no real existence in the complete consciousness of that all-upholding One of which he is part. <small> <a name="THRdec1908" href="/udra/udex.htm#THRdec1908"><cite title="source">The Theosophical Review</cite></a> (December 1908), Unsigned, &ldquo;Queries and Notes. VII&rdquo; 369</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
